<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
The specific epithet is derived from 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">cortadera</emphasis>
, Spanish for &quot;knife, cutting instrument&quot;, referring to the shape of the large sclerotized plates found on the phallus apex.
</paragraph>
